GNU General Public License version 3 (see LICENSE).

Modifications in this fork
--------------------------

1. Complete Japanese (ja-JP) localization covering the full WPF UI
   surface (Views, Controls, and user-facing code-behind messages).
2. Runtime language dictionary swap via `App.ChangeLanguage` that mirrors
   the existing `App.ChangeTheme` pattern. Startup priority:
     GRZY_CLOTHTOOL_LANG env var > Settings.Default.Language > "ja".
3. `LocalizationHelper` utility for C# callers (`Get`, `GetFormat`).
4. Bug fixes:
   - Replaced `NotImplementedException` in ConvertBack of three
     IValueConverters (CompressionFormatConverter, IntToVisibilityConverter,
     NullOrEmptyToFalseConverter) with `Binding.DoNothing` to prevent a
     latent crash if the bindings are ever changed to TwoWay.
   - Replaced silently-swallowed `catch { }` blocks in
     Helpers/UpdateHelper.cs with logging (Debug.WriteLine + Sentry) so
     update failures are observable.
5. Hardening / defensive refactors:
   - Removed `Task.Delay().Wait()` busy-wait in DuplicateDetector and
     the install-failure sleep in UpdateHelper (`Thread.Sleep` now).
   - Replaced `NotImplementedException` on live BuildWindow paths with
     `ArgumentOutOfRangeException`.
   - Guarded OptimizeWindow `int.Parse` on the texture-size ComboBox
     with `int.TryParse`.
   - Wrapped the App unhandled-exception log writers so a secondary
     IO failure cannot mask the original crash.
   - Replaced bare `catch { }` in ProjectWindow and Home_Loaded with
     logged / localized error reporting.

Fixed upstream issues in this fork
----------------------------------

The following upstream issues have root-cause fixes in this fork:

  - grzybeek/grzyClothTool#55 "Unchecking 'Hides Hair' doesn't work".
    `GDrawable.Flags` / `SelectedFlags` were both `[JsonIgnore]`, so no
    flag state survived a save+reload. Flags are now persisted and
    rebuilt on load.
  - grzybeek/grzyClothTool#56 "3D Preview error: Failed to update
    drawables in 3D preview". `PreviewWindowHost.UpdateDrawables` now
    tolerates a null value stored in `LoadedDrawables`.
  - grzybeek/grzyClothTool#50 "Crashes on startup" (partial). The
    unhandled-exception log writers no longer crash-in-crash on IO
    failure, and upstream mitigations are inherited.

Known issues inherited from upstream (not yet fixed in this fork)
---------------------------------------------------------------

  - grzybeek/grzyClothTool#49 "RPF_INVALID_ENTRY_4: Empty archive
    entry name" (archive edge case in CodeWalker; bundled binary).
  - grzybeek/grzyClothTool#46 "Male ped has female invisible drawable
    numbers showed in preview" (requires Windows repro).

